cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.NT, cs.MA, cs.SY

This paper deals with the degrees of freedom (DoF) of full-duplex (FD) cellular networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network architecture (cs.NI). The use of reconfigurable antennas also involves antenna theory (cs.NT). The paper also discusses the impact of user-to-user interference, which falls under the category of system and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new achievable sum DoF for partial channel state information, which could be considered as a machine learning approach (cs.MA).
